definition: to reschedule/to rearrange (e.g. a meeting)/to postpone
a period of time/phase/stage/classifier for issues of a periodical, courses of study/time/term/period/to hope/Taiwan pr. [qi2]

sentences.english: Transfers are not permitted within 10 working days of the test.
sentences.chinese: 若在考前10个工作日之内，改期是不允许的。

sentences.english: A: Do you know the picnic has to be put off once again?
sentences.chinese: 你知道野餐活动又得改期了吗？

sentences.english: Flights were available, but often rescheduled or canceled later in the day.
sentences.chinese: 航班是存在的，可是经常在当天改期或是取消。

sentences.english: Sevilla want to change the date because of a festival in the city.
sentences.chinese: 塞维利亚因为同一天在城市内有庆祝节日而希望改期。

sentences.english: Our meetings have been repeatedly rescheduled, month after month.
sentences.chinese: 我们的会面已经一再改期，上月推下月。

sentences.english: It’s the first time in US history that an execution attempt by lethal injection has had to be rescheduled.
sentences.chinese: 这是美国历史上首次出现注射死刑被迫改期的情况。

sentences.english: Semi-final dates for the Belgian Cup have been moved to avoid clashes with international weeks.
sentences.chinese: 比利时杯的半决赛会为避开国家队比赛日而改期。

sentences.english: I was calling to change our meeting next week.
sentences.chinese: 我们下星期的见面，我想改期。

definition: to change one's reservation/to transfer to a different flight, airline, bus or train
to bounce (a check)/to return a ticket/ticket refund
to cancel (a booking)/to unsubscribe (from a newsletter etc)
to reserve a seat/to book a table/reservation
